<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4809] docker/run_tests.sh should set up /opt/kafka-dev to be the source directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4809</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;docker/run_tests.sh }} should be able to run {{sanity_checks/test_verifiable_producer.py&lt;/tt&gt; against version 0.8.2.2.  Currently, it can&apos;t do that, because the Docker image configures the contents of &lt;tt&gt;/opt/kafka-dev&lt;/tt&gt; differently than the Vagrant images are configured.  Currently, &lt;tt&gt;run_tests.sh&lt;/tt&gt; decompresses the &lt;tt&gt;releaseTarGz&lt;/tt&gt; in that directory.  But it should simply be the source directory.  This would also make it unnecessary to copy the &lt;tt&gt;releaseTarGz&lt;/tt&gt; around.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
